cs1302.interfaces.contract

Interface Styleable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicFancy, Fancy, SuperFancy

    public interface Styleable
    This class represents the interface for an object that can be styled and unstyled. The expectation is that the toString() method of a styled object behaves normally. Once an object is styled via style(), the toString() method produces some styled string representation. In order to have the toString() method revert to its normal behavior, the object must be unstyled via unstyle(). This imposes a state requirement on the underlying object (i.e., styled or unstyled) that is left to the implementation.

        Styles the object. This method has no effect if the object is already styled.
